# ============================================
# GOOGLE OAUTH CONFIGURATION (REQUIRED FOR GOOGLE SIGN-IN)
# ============================================
# 
# To enable the Google Sign-In button:
#
# 1. Visit: https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
# 2. Create a new project or select an existing one
# 3. Click "+ CREATE CREDENTIALS" → "OAuth 2.0 Client ID"
# 4. Configure consent screen if prompted
# 5. Application type: Web application
# 6. Add http://localhost:5173 to "Authorized JavaScript origins"
# 7. Copy your Client ID and paste it below (replace the placeholder)
#
# See GOOGLE_OAUTH_SETUP.md for detailed instructions with screenshots
#
# Format: XXXXXXXXXX-XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX.apps.googleusercontent.com
#
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=926382572179-t9oe2nv0u5hplmif9p5suq9spuq2iqes.apps.googleusercontent.com

# API Configuration
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:8000/api
